{"title_page": "Ecclesia orans", "text_new": "{{Orphan|date=June 2017}}\n{{italic title}}\n[[File:The cover of Ecclesia orans.jpg|thumb|The cover of ''Ecclesia orans'']]\n'''''Ecclesia orans: Periodica de Scientiis Liturgicis''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] on all aspects of [[Christian liturgy]] published by the [[Pontifical Institute of Sacred Liturgy]] of [[Sant'Anselmo all'Aventino]].<ref name=F /><ref name=G /><ref name=D /><ref name=E /> It was established in 1984 and appeared triannually.<ref name=F /><ref name=D /><ref name=E /> Since 2013 it has been published biannually. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Markus Tymister ([[Pontifical Atheneum of St. Anselm]]). Articles are published in English, French, German, Italian, Portuguese, and Spanish.\n\n==Editors-in-chief== \nThe following persons are or have been editors-in chief:\n*[[Adrien Nocent]] [[Order of Saint Benedict|OSB]] (1984-1996)<ref name=D /><ref name=E />\n*[[Anscar Chupungco]] OSB (1997)<ref name=E />\n*Cassian Folsom OSB (1997-1998)<ref name=E />\n*Ephrem Carr OSB (1999-2012)<ref name=E />\n*Pietro Angelo Muroni (2012\u20132018)<ref name=E />\n*Markus Tymister (2018\u2013present)\n\n==Abstracting and indexing==\nThe journal is abstracted and indexed in the [[ATLA Religion Database]]<ref name=ATLA>{{cite web |url=https://www.atla.com/products/titles/Pages/default.aspx |title=Title and Product Update Lists |publisher=[[American Theological Library Association]] |work=[[ATLA Religion Database]] |accessdate=2019-01-09}}</ref> and in 2012 and 2014 in [[Scopus]].<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=https://www.scopus.com/sourceid/21100281306 |title=Source details: Ecclesia orans |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus preview |accessdate=2019-01-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|\nrefs=\n<ref name=D>Chupungco A., ''The Pontifical Liturgical Institute: a Benedictine service to the Church'', in: G.J. B\u00e9k\u00e9s (ed.), ''Sant'Anselmo. Saggi storici e di attualit\u00e0'', Benedictina - Edizioni Abbazia S. Paolo, Roma 1988, 193-226, {{ISBN|88-8139-057-4}}.</ref>\n<ref name=E>Muroni P.A., \"Ecclesia orans\" 30 anni a servizio della Scientia liturgica, ''Rivista liturgica'' 4/2013: 951-956, Edizioni Messaggero Padova (Italian).</ref>\n<ref name=F>Engelbert P., ''Sant'Anselmo a Roma - Collegio e ateneo: Dagli inizi (1888) fino ad oggi'', Eos Verlag U. Druck, 2013 (Italian).</ref>\n<ref name=G>Penco G., ''Il monachesimo fra spiritualit\u00e0 e cultura'', Jaca Book, Milano 1991, 355, {{ISBN|88-16-30199-6}} (Italian).</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.ecclesiaorans.com/}}\n*{{ISSN|1010-3872}}\n\n[[Category:1984 establishments in Italy]]\n[[Category:Biannual journals]]\n[[Category:Publications established in 1984]]\n[[Category:Multilingual journals]]\n", "text_old": "{{Orphan|date=June 2017}}\n{{italic title}}\n[[File:The cover of Ecclesia orans.jpg|thumb|The cover of ''Ecclesia orans'']]\n'''''Ecclesia orans: Periodica de Scientiis Liturgicis''''' is a [[peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] on all aspects of [[Christian liturgy]] published by the [[Pontifical Institute of Sacred Liturgy]] of [[Sant'Anselmo all'Aventino]].<ref name=F /><ref name=G /><ref name=D /><ref name=E /> It was established in 1984 and appeared triannually.<ref name=F /><ref name=D /><ref name=E /> Since 2013 it has been published biannually. The [[editor-in-chief]] is Markus Tymister ([[Pontifical Atheneum of St. Anselm]]). Articles are pu blished in English, French, German, Italian, Portuguese, and Spanish.\n\n==Editors-in-chief== \nThe following persons are or have been editors-in chief:\n*[[Adrien Nocent]] [[Order of Saint Benedict|OSB]] (1984-1996)<ref name=D /><ref name=E />\n*[[Anscar Chupungco]] OSB (1997)<ref name=E />\n*Cassian Folsom OSB (1997-1998)<ref name=E />\n*Ephrem Carr OSB (1999-2012)<ref name=E />\n*Pietro Angelo Muroni (2012\u20132018)<ref name=E />\n*Markus Tymister (2018\u2013present)\n\n==Abstracting and indexing==\nThe journal is abstracted and indexed in the [[ATLA Religion Database]]<ref name=ATLA>{{cite web |url=https://www.atla.com/products/titles/Pages/default.aspx |title=Title and Product Update Lists |publisher=[[American Theological Library Association]] |work=[[ATLA Religion Database]] |accessdate=2019-01-09}}</ref> and in 2012 and 2014 in [[Scopus]].<ref name=Scopus>{{cite web |url=https://www.scopus.com/sourceid/21100281306 |title=Source details: Ecclesia orans |publisher=[[Elsevier]] |work=Scopus preview |accessdate=2019-01-09}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|\nrefs=\n<ref name=D>Chupungco A., ''The Pontifical Liturgical Institute: a Benedictine service to the Church'', in: G.J. B\u00e9k\u00e9s (ed.), ''Sant'Anselmo. Saggi storici e di attualit\u00e0'', Benedictina - Edizioni Abbazia S. Paolo, Roma 1988, 193-226, {{ISBN|88-8139-057-4}}.</ref>\n<ref name=E>Muroni P.A., \"Ecclesia orans\" 30 anni a servizio della Scientia liturgica, ''Rivista liturgica'' 4/2013: 951-956, Edizioni Messaggero Padova (Italian).</ref>\n<ref name=F>Engelbert P., ''Sant'Anselmo a Roma - Collegio e ateneo: Dagli inizi (1888) fino ad oggi'', Eos Verlag U. Druck, 2013 (Italian).</ref>\n<ref name=G>Penco G., ''Il monachesimo fra spiritualit\u00e0 e cultura'', Jaca Book, Milano 1991, 355, {{ISBN|88-16-30199-6}} (Italian).</ref>\n}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.ecclesiaorans.com/}}\n*{{ISSN|1010-3872}}\n\n[[Category:1984 establishments in Italy]]\n[[Category:Biannual journals]]\n[[Category:Publications established in 1984]]\n[[Category:Multilingual journals]]\n", "name_user": "Rbstrachan", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fixed typo.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecclesia_orans"}
{"title_page": "Victor Walters", "text_new": "{{short description|English footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Victor Walters\n| image          =\n| fullname       =\n| birth_date     = \n| birth_place    = England\n| death_date     = '\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| years1         = 1913\u20131914| clubs1 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester Fosse]]| caps1 = 11  |goals1 = 2\n}}\n'''Victor Walters''' was an [[English people|English]] [[association football|footballer]] who played in [[the Football League]] for [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester Fosse]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Joyce|first=Michael|title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939|year=2004|publisher=SoccerData|isbn=1-899468-67-6}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Walters, Victor}}\n[[Category:Year of birth unknown]]\n[[Category:Date of death unknown]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Leicester City F.C. players]]\n[[Category:English Football League players]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{England-footy-forward-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|English footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2016}}\n{{Use British English|date=April 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name           = Victor Walters\n| image          =\n| fullname       =\n| birth_date     = \n| birth_place    = England\n| death_date     = '\n| position       = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n| years1         = 1913\u20131914| clubs1 = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester Fosse]]| caps1 = 11  |goals1 = 2\n}}\n'''Victor Walters''' was an [[English people|English]] [[association football|footballer]] who played in [[the Football League]] for [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester Fosse]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Joyce|first=Michael|title=Football League Players' Records 1888 to 1939|year=2004|publisher=SoccerData|isbn=1-899468-67-6}}</ref>\n\n==